    <body>
        
        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <date>12.i | 82</date>
                    <salute>Dear Sir</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
                    <p>My father is very glad to lend you Weismann, and hopes that you will keep it as long as it is of any use to you<ref target="#foot.f1"/></p>
<p>Yours faithfully | Francis Darwin</p> 
                </div>
            </div>

            
        </div>
        
        
        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">Meldola had requested a copy of <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_5050.xml">August Weismann</ref>’s paper on daphnids (<ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_11589.xml">Weismann 1878</ref>; see <ref target="./DCP-LETT-13609.xml">letter from Raphael Meldola, 11 January 1882</ref> and n. 1).</note>

            
        </div>
    
    </body>
